name: Communication construction
information: designing the layout of energy distribution, water pipes and ventilation systems and identifying relevant materials

name: Construction team management
information: Liaising with the architect, surveyors and other construction professionals, sometimes managing the design project team

name: System tests
information: Сarrying out tests on systems and making changes to plans where necessary

name: Environmental legislation and initiatives
information: Keeping up to date with relevant changes in environmental legislation and initiatives including international legislation where applicable

name: Constraining factors
information: Working around constraining factors such as town planning legislation, environmental impact and project budget

name: Environmental performance data
information: Assessing, analysing and collating environmental performance data and reporting information to internal staff, clients and regulatory bodies

name: Overseeing the work
information: Overseeing the work of building surveyors and providing them with supportive management

name: Presentations and reports
information: Giving presentations and writing reports highlighting the practical implications of the architect’s designs

name: Energy effaceency
information: Promoting energy efficiency and other sustainability initiatives

name: Environment Agency communication
information: Liaising with regulatory bodies such as the Environment Agency
